The paper deals with learning network games, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of optimization techniques to learn the structure of the network, which falls under optimization (cs.SI) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implications of the proposed approach for understanding strategic interactions in a network environment, which falls under social and information networks (cs.SOC).
